Early pregnancy vitamin D status is associated with blood pressure in children: An Odense Child Cohort study.
The mean (SD) 5-year SBP/DBP was 101.0/63.8 (7.1/5.9) mmHg. In adjusted analyses, a 10 nmol/L increase of s-25(OH)D in early pregnancy associated with a 0.3/0.2 mmHg lower SBP/DBP at 5 years (p 75 nmol/L, were inversely associated with 5-year blood pressure in the offspring. A novel identified protective effect of optimal vitamin D levels in early pregnancy on offspring BP is suggested.
